/wiki/Berovo: Berovo ( Macedonian : Берово [ ˈbɛrɔvɔ ] ( listen ) ) is a small town near the Maleševo Mountains , 161 km ( 100 mi ) from Skopje , 47 km ( 29 mi ) from Strumica and 52 km ( 32 mi ) from Kočani , in North Macedonia . It is the seat of Berovo Municipality .
/wiki/Berovo_Municipality: Berovo ( Macedonian : Берово [ ˈbɛrɔvɔ ] ( listen ) ) is a municipality in eastern part of Republic of North Macedonia . Berovo is also the name of the town where the municipal seat is found . Berovo Municipality is part of the Eastern Statistical Region .
/wiki/Del\u010devo: Delčevo ( Macedonian : Делчево [ ˈdɛɫtʃɛvɔ ] ( listen ) ) is a small town in the eastern mountainous part of North Macedonia . It is the municipal seat of the eponymous municipality . A festival in celebration of Macedonian revolutionary leader Gotse Delchev is held every year on August 2 .
/wiki/Del\u010devo_Municipality: Delčevo Municipality ( Macedonian : Делчево [ ˈdɛɫtʃɛvɔ ] ( listen ) ) is a municipality in the eastern part of the Republic of North Macedonia . The seat is found at the town of Delčevo . Delčevo Municipality is part of the Eastern Statistical Region .
/wiki/Ko\u010dani: Kočani ( Macedonian : Кочани [ ˈkɔtʃani ] ( listen ) ) is a town in the eastern part of North Macedonia , 120 kilometres ( 75 mi ) from Skopje . It has a population of 38,092 and is the seat of the Kočani Municipality
/wiki/Ko\u010dani_Municipality: Kočani ( Macedonian : Кочани [ ˈkɔtʃani ] ( listen ) ) is a municipality in eastern part of the Republic of North Macedonia . Kočani is also the name of the town where the municipal seat is found . The municipality is part of the Eastern Statistical Region .
/wiki/Makedonska_Kamenica: Makedonska Kamenica ( Macedonian : Македонска Каменица [ maˈkɛdɔnska kaˈmɛnitsa ] ( listen ) ) is a town in the north-east of North Macedonia . It has 5,147 inhabitants , the majority of whom are ethnic Macedonians . The town is the seat of Makedonska Kamenica Municipality .
/wiki/Makedonska_Kamenica_Municipality: Makedonska Kamenica ( Macedonian : Македонска Каменица [ maˈkɛdɔnska kaˈmɛnitsa ] ( listen ) ) is a municipality in eastern North Macedonia . Makedonska Kamenica is also the name of the town where the municipal seat is found . The municipality is part of Eastern Statistical Region .
/wiki/Peh\u010devo: Pehčevo ( Macedonian : Пехчево , [ ˈpɛxtʃɛvɔ ] ( listen ) is a small town in the eastern part of North Macedonia . It is the seat of Pehčevo Municipality . In 2002 , the town had 3,193 residents .
/wiki/Peh\u010devo_Municipality: Pehčevo Municipality ( Macedonian : Општина Пехчево [ ˈpɛxtʃɛvɔ ] ( listen ) ) is a municipality in the eastern part of the Republic of North Macedonia . Pehčevo is also the name of the town where the municipal seat is found . This municipality is part of the Eastern Statistical Region .
/wiki/Probi\u0161tip: Probištip ( Macedonian : Пробиштип [ ˈprɔbiʃtip ] ( listen ) ) is a town in North Macedonia , and seat of Probištip Municipality . The town has a population of 10,826 .
/wiki/Probi\u0161tip_Municipality: Probištip Municipality ( Macedonian : Општина Пробиштип [ ˈprɔbiʃtip ] ( listen ) ) is an urban municipality in eastern Republic of North Macedonia . Probištip is also the name of the city where the municipal seat is found . This municipality is part of the Eastern Statistical Region .
/wiki/\u0160tip: Štip ( Macedonian : Штип [ ʃtip ] ( listen ) ) is the largest urban agglomeration in the eastern part of North Macedonia , serving as the economic , industrial , entertainment and educational focal point for the surrounding municipalities . As of the 2002 census , the Štip municipality alone had a population of about 47,796 . Štip is the largest textile production center in the country ; Center of the fashion industry in North Macedonia , as well as the location of the sole public university in eastern North Macedonia , Goce Delčev University of Štip . The city of Štip is the seat of Štip Municipality .
/wiki/\u0160tip_Municipality: Štip ( Macedonian : Штип [ ʃtip ] ( listen ) ) is a municipality in eastern Republic of North Macedonia . Štip is also the name of the town where the municipal seat is found . This municipality is part of the Eastern Statistical Region .
/wiki/Vinica,_Macedonia: Vinica ( Macedonian : Виница [ ˈvinitsa ] ( listen ) ) is a town in North Macedonia , in the Eastern Statistical Region of the country . The town of Vinica is the seat of Vinica Municipality .
/wiki/Vinica_Municipality,_Macedonia: Vinica ( Macedonian : Виница [ ˈvinitsa ] ( listen ) ) is a municipality in eastern part of North Macedonia . Vinica is also the name of the town where the municipal seat is found . Vinica Municipality is part of the Eastern Statistical Region .
